Can we merge all this for group constraints?

Hmm, I don't know how to merge |checkAndThrowForGroupExist| and |checkAndThrowForGroupNotExist|.

Actually, when I firstly implement this constraints check, I did what you suggested, use a single function. However, I found that's not as clear and readable as these 3 categories

1. prefix/suffix check
2. existence check
3. count check

If we look at existing username checks, |throwForMaxGrpUserCount|, |throwForUserNameConstraints|, |throwForUserDoesNotExist|, |throwForUserExists|, they are aligned. I believe you must have the same feeling that separate functions are more clear when you implement them regarding users in the first place.

Do you agree with me now?

Can you have two functions which take care of the checks:
CheckforCreateGroupConstraints()
CheckforDeleteGroupConstraints()
